<critical requirement>
The Test Suite Reviewer shall perform a coverage assessment
for the input requirement.
Context: The coverage assessment is guided by three aspects
of requirement verification: Functional, Alternative/Negative, and
Boundary/Edge. Functional coverage is the primary dimension in determining
whether a test suite adequately verifies the intended behavior.
Alternative/Negative tests validate robustness and error handling pathways
critical to safe operation. Boundary tests are essential to detect defects
at value limits and edge conditions.
</critical requirement>
